explanation:
A class is a template — you can stamp out as many objects as needed, each with its own data.

Example:
```csharp
var d1 = new Dog { Name = "Rex" };
var d2 = new Dog { Name = "Bella" };
```

Put risky code in `try`. If an exception occurs, execution jumps to `catch` where you handle the error gracefully.

Example:
```csharp
try { int x = int.Parse("abc"); }
catch (FormatException e) { Console.WriteLine(e.Message); }
```
